{"info": {"author": "Ray Douglass", "author_email": "ray@raydouglass.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# search-fs\n\nA simple python utility that indexes directory and file names in a sqlite database to allow for fast searching.\n\nDefinitely check out [locate](http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man1/locate.1.html) before considering this tool.\n\n## Installation\n\n```shell script\npip install search-fs\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```shell script\ncreate-search-fs --help\nsearch-fs --help\n```\n\n### Create the database\n\n```shell script\ncreate-search-fs dir1/ dir2/\n```\n\n### Search\n\nSearch anywhere for JPG files\n```shell script\nsearch-fs --name '*.jpg'\n```\n\nSearch just one directory tree for JPG files\n```shell script\nsearch-fs --name '*.jpg' dir1/\n```\n\nSearch just one directory and not any of the sub directories for JPG files\n```shell script\nsearch-fs --name '*.jpg' dir1/ --strict-dir\n```\n\nSearch for directories\n```shell script\nsearch-fs --name 'Directory*' --type d\n```\n\nSearch for files by size\n```shell script\nsearch-fs --size '500M' #Files larger than 500MB\nsearch-fs --size='-10M' #Files smaller than 10MB, Note: make sure you use use '--size=' for less than\n```\n\n### Cron\n\nYou can setup a cronjob to run `create-search-fs` so that the index is up to date.\n\nCreate `dirs.txt` which contains the directories to index\n\n```\n#Lines starting with # are ignored\n/path/dir1\n/other/dir2\n```\n\nAdd line with `crontab -e` to update the index every hour\n\n```shell script\n0 * * * * /usr/local/bin/create-search-fs --dirs /path/to/dirs.txt\n```\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/raydouglass/search-fs", "keywords": "", "license": "Apache", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "search-fs", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/search-fs/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/search-fs/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/raydouglass/search-fs"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/search-fs/0.0.3/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=3.6", "summary": "Scripts for managing media", "version": "0.0.3", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>search-fs</h1>\n<p>A simple python utility that indexes directory and file names in a sqlite database to allow for fast searching.</p>\n<p>Definitely check out <a href=\"http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man1/locate.1.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">locate</a> before considering this tool.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<pre>pip install search-fs\n</pre>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre>create-search-fs --help\nsearch-fs --help\n</pre>\n<h3>Create the database</h3>\n<pre>create-search-fs dir1/ dir2/\n</pre>\n<h3>Search</h3>\n<p>Search anywhere for JPG files</p>\n<pre>search-fs --name <span class=\"s1\">'*.jpg'</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Search just one directory tree for JPG files</p>\n<pre>search-fs --name <span class=\"s1\">'*.jpg'</span> dir1/\n</pre>\n<p>Search just one directory and not any of the sub directories for JPG files</p>\n<pre>search-fs --name <span class=\"s1\">'*.jpg'</span> dir1/ --strict-dir\n</pre>\n<p>Search for directories</p>\n<pre>search-fs --name <span class=\"s1\">'Directory*'</span> --type d\n</pre>\n<p>Search for files by size</p>\n<pre>search-fs --size <span class=\"s1\">'500M'</span> <span class=\"c1\">#Files larger than 500MB</span>\nsearch-fs --size<span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s1\">'-10M'</span> <span class=\"c1\">#Files smaller than 10MB, Note: make sure you use use '--size=' for less than</span>\n</pre>\n<h3>Cron</h3>\n<p>You can setup a cronjob to run <code>create-search-fs</code> so that the index is up to date.</p>\n<p>Create <code>dirs.txt</code> which contains the directories to index</p>\n<pre><code>#Lines starting with # are ignored\n/path/dir1\n/other/dir2\n</code></pre>\n<p>Add line with <code>crontab -e</code> to update the index every hour</p>\n<pre><span class=\"m\">0</span> * * * * /usr/local/bin/create-search-fs --dirs /path/to/dirs.txt\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6724712, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "6e13cad3b36c34e5f3bc389067f020ef", "sha256": "8db1b28402ed3ca72516ac51bc23a7f47181e7cce29a57135f44c59ea66e28a3"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "search_fs-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "6e13cad3b36c34e5f3bc389067f020ef", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6", "size": 8816, "upload_time": "2020-02-27T04:07:43", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-27T04:07:43.024835Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/f5/07/0fe4e6232e956637b79918e9229e971958e7031cad496b1548abd5573432/search_fs-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "de6f74c1a3778957df55e608c764d076", "sha256": "a2186e441c257d0c9df645a18989647106ed7a3536476361fc28b6d1aee3f369"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "search-fs-0.0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "de6f74c1a3778957df55e608c764d076", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.6", "size": 3538, "upload_time": "2020-02-27T04:07:45", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-27T04:07:45.206882Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/e6/3b/b93b44623a9c8f19d3f71fc9658ffb4d698cb7ff4b3886493160e6fb2c52/search-fs-0.0.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "5187c9b6f036e737bafe6ed10e256621", "sha256": "2280505740e5ef745849215958361f251a7a04206afa82a3dc16375575f4ecd2"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "search_fs-0.0.2-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "5187c9b6f036e737bafe6ed10e256621", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_